1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:03,599
Thame, I've figured out who's been helping you.

2
00:00:03,679 --> 00:00:04,640
Where are you?

3
00:00:04,720 --> 00:00:05,760
Are you still at the set?

4
00:00:05,840 --> 00:00:07,120
What did you say to him?

5
00:00:07,199 --> 00:00:09,320
Why did he agree to come back and do this for the others again?

6
00:00:09,400 --> 00:00:11,200
He should have learned to be selfish sometimes.

7
00:00:11,280 --> 00:00:12,719
He's bringing the group back together

8
00:00:12,799 --> 00:00:15,520
to make up for the leadership he failed to provide.

9
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:17,080
Since your friend is being this selfish,

10
00:00:17,160 --> 00:00:18,439
don't you want to support him somehow?

11
00:00:18,520 --> 00:00:20,720
Thanks for going back to the group's house.

12
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:22,480
Don't think I'm into it or something. Please, okay?

13
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:23,680
No one lives there.

14
00:00:23,759 --> 00:00:24,959
Why wouldn't I stay?

15
00:00:25,560 --> 00:00:27,880
I cleared things up with him already, but I've got a new problem now.

16
00:00:27,959 --> 00:00:30,119
I don't have your number. Tell me your number.

17
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:31,599
I'll remember every single digit.

18
00:00:31,680 --> 00:00:32,879
I don't want to forget it.

19
00:00:46,600 --> 00:00:48,839
I told you, he's the easiest one to come back.

20
00:00:48,919 --> 00:00:50,680
I've got one point now.

21
00:00:50,760 --> 00:00:52,040
You guys handle the rest.

22
00:00:54,800 --> 00:00:57,120
You want me to help bring Nano back first, right?

23
00:01:02,480 --> 00:01:03,519
Dylan.

24
00:01:05,360 --> 00:01:06,480
Dylan?

25
00:02:37,239 --> 00:02:40,359
THAME.TEEMA: I NEED YOUR HELP.

26
00:02:40,440 --> 00:02:44,280
WHY DID YOU READ MY MESSAGE SO FAST?

27
00:02:46,959 --> 00:02:50,359
MY HAND ACCIDENTALLY HIT THE SCREEN SO, WHAT'S UP?

28
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:51,400
Whoa!

29
00:02:57,519 --> 00:02:59,160
What's with that face?

30
00:02:59,239 --> 00:03:01,320
Aren't you excited to see me?

31
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:03,760
Why should I be?

32
00:03:04,519 --> 00:03:05,840
Is there anything I should be excited about?

33
00:03:07,320 --> 00:03:09,040
What makes Thame confident

34
00:03:09,120 --> 00:03:10,399
that someone like you can help?

35
00:03:11,079 --> 00:03:12,480
What does Thame want me to help with?

36
00:03:23,679 --> 00:03:25,519
There are two things we need to split up and look for.

37
00:03:28,920 --> 00:03:30,359
You need to find where Dylan is

38
00:03:31,760 --> 00:03:33,920
because no one has been able to reach him,

39
00:03:35,560 --> 00:03:36,799
except Mick.

40
00:03:39,040 --> 00:03:39,880
Well…

41
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:42,920
As for me,

42
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:46,040
I must get the storage room key to look for a specific song.

43
00:03:46,600 --> 00:03:49,040
Why do you want the storage room key?

44
00:03:51,119 --> 00:03:53,119
I must write a song to sing during my live streaming,

45
00:03:54,440 --> 00:03:57,280
so I want to borrow some old lyrics the company already threw away.

46
00:03:57,359 --> 00:03:58,679
If I just randomly pick one from Cloud,

47
00:03:58,760 --> 00:03:59,679
it might be someone's comeback single.

48
00:04:01,880 --> 00:04:03,880
But it's up to you, then.

49
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:06,160
I can write a new song myself,

50
00:04:06,679 --> 00:04:08,079
but I don't know how it will turn out.

51
00:04:09,880 --> 00:04:10,959
Hold on.

52
00:04:23,960 --> 00:04:25,159
How smart Thame is.

53
00:04:26,599 --> 00:04:29,640
He made you join first because he knew you could really help a lot.

54
00:04:33,479 --> 00:04:35,000
You should have complimented me, shouldn't you?

55
00:04:35,080 --> 00:04:36,080
Has Thame even done anything yet?

56
00:04:39,039 --> 00:04:41,000
Fine. You're smart.

57
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:45,240
You're so smart for being two-faced.

58
00:04:48,840 --> 00:04:50,880
At least I managed to get the hard part done,

59
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:52,960
unlike you,

60
00:04:53,039 --> 00:04:55,280
who can't get anything done right.

61
00:04:55,880 --> 00:04:56,719
Eh?

62
00:04:57,360 --> 00:04:58,680
It's not my fault.

63
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:01,640
That slacker Mick doesn't even work,

64
00:05:02,360 --> 00:05:03,840
so he doesn't know where Dylan is.

65
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:06,280
Just forget about it.

66
00:05:07,840 --> 00:05:09,640
At least the important thing is here.

67
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:11,400
If we can find that song,

68
00:05:11,479 --> 00:05:13,400
Dylan will probably agree to talk.

69
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:16,479
A song?

70
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:18,320
Thame chose to bring Dylan back first

71
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:19,680
because I think he knows

72
00:05:19,760 --> 00:05:21,400
the conflict between them…

73
00:05:23,360 --> 00:05:24,240
…is this.

74
00:05:45,359 --> 00:05:46,479
Oh?

75
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:51,960
So, so many of the songs Dylan composed got rejected by the company?

76
00:05:54,080 --> 00:05:55,280
There are more than this, actually.

77
00:05:55,880 --> 00:05:58,000
Dylan agreed to sign with the company

78
00:05:58,080 --> 00:06:01,200
because at first, he probably thought they liked his songs,

79
00:06:01,280 --> 00:06:02,840
but in reality,

80
00:06:02,919 --> 00:06:05,280
they just wanted a good rapper to add something to an idol group.

81
00:06:12,719 --> 00:06:14,320
That's why he didn't get along with others much,

82
00:06:18,599 --> 00:06:19,880
except with Thame.

83
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:30,159
How about…

84
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:32,359
trying it this way?

85
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:36,599
But it's such a high note.

86
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:38,320
Who could hit it?

87
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:39,240
I could.

88
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:47,840
Not willing to risk it

89
00:06:47,919 --> 00:06:53,240
Can't say goodbye

90
00:06:54,280 --> 00:06:55,880
From not coming to the group's house at all,

91
00:06:56,799 --> 00:06:58,120
he agreed to come because of Thame.

92
00:07:01,880 --> 00:07:03,320
Thame once mentioned

93
00:07:03,919 --> 00:07:05,520
he'd finally make Dylan a PD.

94
00:07:12,560 --> 00:07:14,520
-That's why he agreed to stay, -Dammit. This works.

95
00:07:14,599 --> 00:07:16,440
believing Thame could really make it happen.

96
00:07:16,520 --> 00:07:17,359
Nice.

97
00:07:17,440 --> 00:07:19,039
Let's keep it on the hard disk,

98
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:21,599
because if we add it on Cloud, it will become Oner's.

99
00:07:23,120 --> 00:07:24,120
Hold on.

100
00:07:24,919 --> 00:07:29,039
Are you saying that song was…

101
00:07:30,280 --> 00:07:31,719
I want us to produce this single for MARS.

102
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:33,359
It's the song that…

103
00:07:34,440 --> 00:07:35,280
CAN I MAKE YOU MINE?

104
00:07:35,359 --> 00:07:36,640
He made it with Dylan.

105
00:07:37,640 --> 00:07:39,599
We aren't going to do it, Thame.

106
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:42,239
But I fixed it with…

107
00:07:43,359 --> 00:07:44,200
Dylan.

108
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:50,520
Done, done, done.

109
00:07:52,359 --> 00:07:54,400
Part of the reason Thame's been pushing himself so hard

110
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:57,080
is for Dylan's song to be accepted.

111
00:07:57,159 --> 00:07:58,679
This one will do.

112
00:07:58,760 --> 00:08:00,200
-It's exactly this one. -Write it down.

113
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:01,359
-Write it down now. -Okay.

114
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:04,479
But yeah,

115
00:08:05,760 --> 00:08:07,239
when it didn't really happen,

116
00:08:08,679 --> 00:08:10,799
the person who felt the most betrayed…

117
00:08:11,479 --> 00:08:12,560
Thame!

118
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:15,120
-Dylan! -Dylan, calm down!

119
00:08:15,200 --> 00:08:16,719
-…is Dylan. -Hey!

120
00:08:17,320 --> 00:08:18,440
Why the hell should I calm myself down?

121
00:08:18,520 --> 00:08:19,960
Can't you see?

122
00:08:20,039 --> 00:08:21,359
He's betraying all of us!

123
00:08:23,359 --> 00:08:25,520
You're fucking fake!

124
00:08:33,439 --> 00:08:34,439
Dylan!

125
00:08:34,520 --> 00:08:35,720
-Dylan! -Dylan!

126
00:08:37,520 --> 00:08:38,559
Dylan!

127
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:43,480
Actually,

128
00:08:45,280 --> 00:08:47,000
knowing that Thame is reuniting the group,

129
00:08:48,040 --> 00:08:49,840
Dylan was supposed to be happy about it, wasn't he?

130
00:08:51,640 --> 00:08:56,760
Dylan is not the type to take a risk with someone who's betrayed him once.

131
00:08:58,360 --> 00:09:01,280
That's why Pepper and I told Thame

132
00:09:01,360 --> 00:09:04,040
it's really hard to bring Dylan back first,

133
00:09:05,079 --> 00:09:06,720
but Thame insisted.

134
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:09,079
Trust me,

135
00:09:09,160 --> 00:09:11,240
we really have to bring Dylan back first,

136
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:14,439
no matter how hard it is.

137
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:17,199
I'm not sure what's on his mind.

138
00:09:22,760 --> 00:09:23,839
Check over there first.

139
00:09:41,360 --> 00:09:43,040
I'll fetch the one who caused this trouble.

140
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:45,040
Huh?

141
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:50,360
How is everything?

142
00:09:50,959 --> 00:09:52,920
What did you expect us to get, huh? We've just got in here.

143
00:09:53,480 --> 00:09:56,760
You said you split up with Per to look for Dylan, didn't you?

144
00:09:56,839 --> 00:09:58,240
Why did you suddenly show up here?

145
00:09:59,079 --> 00:10:01,600
I already did, but couldn't find him.

146
00:10:03,839 --> 00:10:06,040
Hey. Po, how is it going?

147
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:11,640
Well,

148
00:10:13,040 --> 00:10:15,240
this is what I found.

149
00:10:17,040 --> 00:10:18,319
It's not this one.

150
00:10:34,959 --> 00:10:36,240
Thame, Jun.

151
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:19,719
DYLAN

152
00:11:25,040 --> 00:11:26,800
You aren't at the group's house, Thame?

153
00:11:30,040 --> 00:11:30,880
Why?

154
00:11:32,640 --> 00:11:34,079
I'm thinking about coming back to see you.

155
00:11:40,079 --> 00:11:41,040
Yeah.

156
00:11:41,839 --> 00:11:42,920
I'm sorry.

157
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:45,439
After knowing you didn't go to Korea,

158
00:11:45,520 --> 00:11:46,480
I was probably too hot-headed,

159
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:50,880
but after thinking it over, it might be good for me,

160
00:11:51,480 --> 00:11:53,040
so we can produce songs together again.

161
00:11:56,079 --> 00:11:58,480
You're fucking fake!

162
00:12:05,079 --> 00:12:06,280
Well, yeah.

163
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:09,160
That's true.

164
00:12:09,240 --> 00:12:11,839
Eh? What's with that voice?

165
00:12:11,920 --> 00:12:14,079
Aren't you happy I'm back, huh?

166
00:12:15,079 --> 00:12:17,680
Don't tell me you're suspicious

167
00:12:18,280 --> 00:12:20,000
because I came back so easily like this.

168
00:12:22,480 --> 00:12:24,760
I'm not. I just…

169
00:12:26,040 --> 00:12:28,600
Anyway, I'll talk to you there.

170
00:12:28,680 --> 00:12:29,640
Good.

171
00:12:30,640 --> 00:12:31,760
But come alone.

172
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:34,520
Mm-hmm.

173
00:12:40,240 --> 00:12:41,079
Is something up?

174
00:12:43,319 --> 00:12:44,920
Oh,

175
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:46,880
Per called.

176
00:12:47,599 --> 00:12:49,959
I'll see him now.

177
00:12:50,680 --> 00:12:51,560
Please continue looking for it.

178
00:12:54,920 --> 00:12:56,079
Shit. Thame, hold on.

179
00:12:56,760 --> 00:12:59,640
Mick is here. Dammit. Come here. Hide, both of you.

180
00:13:38,079 --> 00:13:38,920
Hey, Mick?

181
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:41,400
What are you doing down here? Are you helping me look for it?

182
00:13:41,480 --> 00:13:42,880
How can you be this kind?

183
00:13:42,959 --> 00:13:44,360
Helping? I'm not doing that.

184
00:13:45,040 --> 00:13:47,560
I just came to check

185
00:13:47,640 --> 00:13:49,640
if there's somewhere I can secretly take a nap.

186
00:13:50,560 --> 00:13:52,560
You can keep looking for it,

187
00:13:52,640 --> 00:13:54,000
no matter how long it takes.

188
00:13:54,079 --> 00:13:56,760
Tell others I came to help you look for it already.

189
00:13:57,880 --> 00:13:58,920
Hey, hold on.

190
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:01,439
Why are you sleeping there? It's covered in dust.

191
00:14:02,160 --> 00:14:03,800
Come with me. I'll help you find it.

192
00:14:03,880 --> 00:14:05,680
I guarantee nobody will find you.

193
00:14:05,760 --> 00:14:07,560
I'm pretty good at lying about how good you're at doing your job.

194
00:14:08,319 --> 00:14:09,319
Come on. Let's go.

195
00:14:27,880 --> 00:14:28,839
Well,

196
00:14:32,599 --> 00:14:34,240
I'm off.

197
00:14:34,319 --> 00:14:35,319
THE 2021 ANNUAL CONCERT DOCUMENT

198
00:14:36,040 --> 00:14:36,959
Yeah.

199
00:14:37,800 --> 00:14:39,839
I'll continue looking for it.

200
00:14:41,880 --> 00:14:42,760
Thank you.

201
00:15:10,319 --> 00:15:11,640
What the hell is damn wrong with you, Thame?!

202
00:15:11,719 --> 00:15:13,040
Dylan!

203
00:15:29,800 --> 00:15:31,560
Thame, I'm too lazy to wait now.

204
00:15:32,400 --> 00:15:34,319
Well, I have a rap battle coming up.

205
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:36,479
What?

206
00:15:37,800 --> 00:15:39,920
Yeah, come join me.

207
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:41,240
Me?

208
00:15:41,319 --> 00:15:43,479
Those jerks always look down on rapper idols,

209
00:15:43,560 --> 00:15:45,520
calling them lousy.

210
00:15:45,599 --> 00:15:47,199
Show them

211
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:48,680
we're the real deal.

212
00:15:49,439 --> 00:15:50,640
Come with me.

213
00:15:54,800 --> 00:15:56,120
Where?

214
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:58,280
I'll send you the location.

215
00:16:08,280 --> 00:16:09,959
Oh, it's so cramped.

216
00:16:11,920 --> 00:16:13,079
You two must have been all squished together.

217
00:16:14,560 --> 00:16:15,400
Hey.

218
00:16:16,319 --> 00:16:17,920
Just so you know,

219
00:16:18,520 --> 00:16:19,959
don't get carried away, okay?

220
00:16:20,959 --> 00:16:22,240
I've noticed it a few times already.

221
00:16:23,680 --> 00:16:25,280
You have a crush on him, don't you?

222
00:16:31,160 --> 00:16:32,640
Thame won't like you.

223
00:16:33,719 --> 00:16:35,000
He likes tiny girls,

224
00:16:35,599 --> 00:16:37,000
not a big guy like you.

225
00:16:40,240 --> 00:16:42,880
If you can't benefit him, he won't care about you.

226
00:16:43,640 --> 00:16:44,479
See?

227
00:16:44,560 --> 00:16:47,240
After Pepper and I joined, does he reply to your message?

228
00:16:48,719 --> 00:16:50,120
Dylan will join soon.

229
00:16:51,120 --> 00:16:52,880
Get ready to be forgotten, bro.

230
00:16:55,400 --> 00:16:56,599
Shut up.

231
00:16:56,680 --> 00:16:57,920
Consider this a warning from me.

232
00:17:07,680 --> 00:17:11,200
COME GET YOUR FRIEND'S CORPSE AT DEXSTROSE

233
00:17:17,040 --> 00:17:19,720
PEPPER

234
00:17:20,319 --> 00:17:21,720
What's up?

235
00:17:21,800 --> 00:17:23,399
Hello, Jun? Is Thame with you?

236
00:17:23,960 --> 00:17:26,480
I think Dylan is definitely messing around with Thame now.

237
00:17:30,159 --> 00:17:32,159
Dylan left a note here.

238
00:17:32,240 --> 00:17:33,720
From what I checked,

239
00:17:33,800 --> 00:17:37,159
this place is an underground rappers' pub.

240
00:17:38,919 --> 00:17:41,240
To join the gang,

241
00:17:41,320 --> 00:17:43,240
you have to be accepted by them first.

242
00:17:43,320 --> 00:17:45,000
Those guys really hate idol rap.

243
00:17:45,080 --> 00:17:46,120
HAVING LOTS OF FANS DOESN'T MEAN THEY'RE TALENTED

244
00:17:46,200 --> 00:17:49,879
They once insulted us for our stupid pop music,

245
00:17:49,960 --> 00:17:51,560
especially Thame,

246
00:17:51,639 --> 00:17:52,520
since he's the most famous member.

247
00:17:52,600 --> 00:17:54,159
THAT'S JUST HOW THE FAKE ENTERTAINMENT INDUSTRY WORKS

248
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:58,680
I think Dylan is tricking Thame into getting trashed there,

249
00:17:58,760 --> 00:17:59,919
so he'll get accepted by that gang.

250
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:01,720
DID THOSE POP IDOLS EVER WRITE THEIR OWN SONGS?

251
00:18:07,760 --> 00:18:10,200
-Per, have you arrived? -Yeah, I'm here.

252
00:18:11,320 --> 00:18:12,840
If you're there already, go find Thame first

253
00:18:17,280 --> 00:18:18,280
Thame,

254
00:18:19,520 --> 00:18:20,520
let's go back.

255
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:22,399
Dylan is really not coming back to join us.

256
00:18:23,120 --> 00:18:24,200
He just tricked you to come here because--

257
00:18:24,280 --> 00:18:25,120
I knew.

258
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:30,560
-You knew, but you still… -Yeah.

259
00:18:33,360 --> 00:18:35,120
Hey? You're here?

260
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:38,320
Thame, let's go on stage.

261
00:18:39,280 --> 00:18:40,320
Yeah.

262
00:18:49,040 --> 00:18:51,520
Dammit. Jun, come here right now.

263
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:53,919
Make some noises!

264
00:18:57,399 --> 00:18:58,760
Okay. That's enough. That's enough.

265
00:18:58,840 --> 00:19:01,080
Today, we have a very special guest

266
00:19:01,159 --> 00:19:04,120
to join the rap battle with us on stage.

267
00:19:04,200 --> 00:19:05,840
He's the leader of a popular idol group.

268
00:19:06,440 --> 00:19:09,120
Give it up for Thame from MARS.

269
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:13,280
Boo!

270
00:19:18,080 --> 00:19:19,480
-So, what's the deal? -I think you should go home.

271
00:19:19,560 --> 00:19:21,080
You or I will go first?

272
00:19:22,159 --> 00:19:23,440
I think I should go first

273
00:19:23,520 --> 00:19:26,480
because from looking at you now,

274
