545
00:35:27,880 --> 00:35:30,240
the two who hate each other the most are my own parents.

546
00:35:32,160 --> 00:35:33,360
That sounds pretty fun.

547
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:36,200
It's super chaotic.

548
00:35:37,040 --> 00:35:38,360
When they first got divorced,

549
00:35:38,440 --> 00:35:40,520
I had to celebrate my birthday twice a year,

550
00:35:40,600 --> 00:35:42,000
New Year twice a year,

551
00:35:42,080 --> 00:35:43,440
and Songkran twice a year.

552
00:35:44,160 --> 00:35:46,000
But now that they're friends,

553
00:35:46,080 --> 00:35:47,560
we gather to celebrate together.

554
00:35:48,120 --> 00:35:49,680
Whenever there's a celebration,

555
00:35:49,759 --> 00:35:51,920
we've got five members, just like your group.

556
00:35:54,000 --> 00:35:55,200
I want to see that.

557
00:35:57,400 --> 00:35:58,480
Are you coming to my house?

558
00:35:59,480 --> 00:36:00,520
Yeah.

559
00:36:00,600 --> 00:36:03,080
If there's a chance, I'd love to.

560
00:36:04,080 --> 00:36:06,480
But… you're an idol.

561
00:36:07,680 --> 00:36:09,080
Can't an idol go to your house?

562
00:36:10,000 --> 00:36:11,560
That's not what I mean.

563
00:36:11,640 --> 00:36:13,319
I'm worried my family will be in shock.

564
00:36:13,400 --> 00:36:16,880
But if your parents like me, I think it will be nice.

565
00:36:18,080 --> 00:36:19,160
Which song is their favorite?

566
00:36:20,080 --> 00:36:21,279
I'll sing it for them there.

567
00:36:23,279 --> 00:36:24,440
They like those old songs

568
00:36:24,520 --> 00:36:27,600
by Jae, Pun, and so on.

569
00:36:27,680 --> 00:36:28,720
I see.

570
00:36:29,560 --> 00:36:30,720
I played them before.

571
00:36:31,400 --> 00:36:33,520
How about you?

572
00:36:34,319 --> 00:36:35,400
What is your favorite song?

573
00:36:38,279 --> 00:36:40,319
Recently, I've been into the song called "Good Time".

574
00:36:41,279 --> 00:36:42,360
I see.

575
00:36:42,440 --> 00:36:43,960
I've never figured out the chords to this song.

576
00:36:45,040 --> 00:36:47,520
Is it a song from a series?

577
00:36:48,680 --> 00:36:49,799
You like this series?

578
00:36:50,880 --> 00:36:51,720
Yeah.

579
00:36:51,799 --> 00:36:53,680
I like watching movies that portray people's lives.

580
00:36:54,640 --> 00:36:56,640
That's why you're working on a documentary.

581
00:36:57,560 --> 00:36:59,839
How about you?

582
00:36:59,920 --> 00:37:00,960
What's your favorite movie genre?

583
00:37:01,960 --> 00:37:04,000
I'm more into reading books.

584
00:37:04,680 --> 00:37:07,279
That's why you can compose songs, right?

585
00:37:07,799 --> 00:37:09,880
I guess so.

586
00:37:09,960 --> 00:37:14,120
I enjoy reading poems and some classic work.

587
00:37:14,880 --> 00:37:16,799
I only enjoy pop style.

588
00:37:16,880 --> 00:37:18,080
I have never read any classic work.

589
00:37:19,120 --> 00:37:22,640
It might be a bit slow and laid-back,

590
00:37:23,400 --> 00:37:25,279
but I like the way the words are used.

591
00:37:26,600 --> 00:37:27,799
I see.

592
00:37:28,480 --> 00:37:29,920
Do you want me to read it out loud for you?

593
00:38:04,839 --> 00:38:07,160
THAME

594
00:38:13,200 --> 00:38:14,200
Thame.

595
00:38:18,640 --> 00:38:20,960
PO

596
00:38:21,040 --> 00:38:22,000
You got up already?

597
00:38:31,279 --> 00:38:36,560
You make the journey

598
00:38:36,640 --> 00:38:40,120
Along the way more beautiful

599
00:38:41,120 --> 00:38:46,200
I'm lucky to have you On this road with me

600
00:38:46,279 --> 00:38:49,359
No matter how far I have to go

601
00:38:49,440 --> 00:38:53,440
A hundred or thousand miles away

602
00:38:54,720 --> 00:38:59,319
The horizon I aim for Could be reached someday

603
00:39:10,080 --> 00:39:12,759
Good time with you

604
00:39:36,160 --> 00:39:37,319
Or could it be a subtle hint

605
00:39:37,400 --> 00:39:38,720
that he won't be returning to the group's house?

606
00:39:39,920 --> 00:39:40,960
I'm thinking

607
00:39:41,839 --> 00:39:42,839
of shifting focus to something else.

608
00:39:43,359 --> 00:39:44,400
Nano?

609
00:39:44,480 --> 00:39:46,400
He's afraid of working as a group again?

610
00:39:47,920 --> 00:39:50,120
Thame is tearing the last page

611
00:39:50,200 --> 00:39:52,400
and rewriting the whole thing with you.
